TITLE: Inserting with Returning Values in Knex.js
DESCRIPTION: Inserts a new row into the 'books' table and returns the 'id' of the newly inserted row. This is useful for retrieving auto-generated IDs or other calculated values after an insert operation. Supported by PostgreSQL, MSSQL, SQLite, and Oracle.
SOURCE: https://github.com/knex/knex/blob/master/docs/src/guide/query-builder.md#_snippet_46

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
// Returns [ { id: 1 } ]
knex('books').returning('id').insert({ title: 'Slaughterhouse Five' });
```

