TITLE: Running Latest Migrations
DESCRIPTION: Runs the latest migrations for the current environment. The `--env` flag or `NODE_ENV` environment variable can be used to specify a different environment (e.g., production).
SOURCE: https://github.com/knex/knex/blob/master/docs/src/guide/migrations.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
$ knex migrate:latest
```

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
$ knex migrate:latest --env production

# or

$ NODE_ENV=production knex migrate:latest
```

