TITLE: Creating Column Check Constraint - checkRegex in Knex.js
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to add a check constraint on a column to ensure that the value matches a specific regular expression, using Knex.js.
SOURCE: https://github.com/knex/knex/blob/master/docs/src/guide/schema-builder.md#_snippet_58

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
knex.schema.createTable('product', function (table) {
  table.string('phone').checkRegex('[0-9]{8}');
  // In MSSQL, {8} syntax don't work,
  // you need to duplicate [0-9].
  table.string('phone').checkRegex('[0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]');
});
```

