TITLE: Implementing Custom Seed Source in Knex.js
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates the implementation of a custom seed source in Knex.js. It defines a class `MySeedSource` with methods to retrieve a list of seed names (`getSeeds`) and the corresponding seed function (`getSeed`). The `getSeeds` method returns a Promise that resolves to an array of seed names. The `getSeed` method takes a seed name as input and returns a Knex seeding function based on the seed name. An instance of this class is then used in the `knex.seed.run` method to execute the seeding process.
